Might sound stupid but, I've always wanted to see someone and give them a lift when they looked like they clearly needed one. This world is too scary now to trust someone to get into my car.... But there was one time I regretted not offering a ride. It was a cold rainy night and I was on my way home from work. This wasn't just small drops, it was fucking raining bullets. I made eye contact with a mom walking on the sidewalk while carrying her small child wrapped in her arms. No umbrella just fully down pouring on them.
